main event: A report from the Department of the Air Force regarding multiple unidentified flying object sightings in Wadena, Minnesota.
interesting points: The Air Force concluded that one observation may have been a celestial object such as a star or planet., A witness described seeing an object for about 5 minutes with a rapid fall near a field., The witness's age was recorded as 11 years old., Handwritten notes indicate possible encounters with underground flying discs dating back to 1936., The report emphasizes the importance of providing as much detail as possible for research purposes.
witness description: An 11-year-old girl and a resident named Marriam R. Wright.
